Ignore all history files under `Only for History Use/` for normative decisions.

The active rules are divided into:

- **`design-system.mdc`** — V7 tokens, typography (**Oswald** headings; **Barlow** / **Barlow Condensed** body and `font-label`), motion, palette, hierarchy.
- **`copy-writing.mdc`** — Copy volume, measure/split rules, component mapping, 40-word tabbed detail rule.
- **`seo-strategy.mdc`** — Metadata patterns, sitemap/robots, JSON-LD, heading discipline, DOM-visible SEO copy.

When editing files matched by those rules’ globs, apply the corresponding module. `master/MASTER_RULES.md` remains a consolidated human-readable V7 reference; keep it aligned when changing normative design or copy law.
